  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In today's technological era, daily life is deeply intertwined with digital innovations, which are even reshaping the foundations of educational practices.",
    "The advent of this digital age has prompted a profound shift in pedagogical approaches, highlighting a new challenge: digital illiteracy.",
    "This term, as discussed by Prodromou (2014), denotes the gap between those who engage with digital technologies and those who remain disconnected.",
    "The educational sector has observed that incorporating technology can foster an environment in which students develop into innovative and autonomous learners.",
    "Thus, the onus is on educators to remodel their teaching strategies from traditional, individualized instruction to more collaborative approaches that encompass the entire school community (Cachia et al., 2010; Wasserman & Millgram, 2005)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This term, as discussed by Prodromou (2014), denotes the gap between those who engage with digital technologies and those who remain disconnected.",
